    "body": "## Problem\n\nRunning `:Man curl` in neovim results in the following error:\n```\nman.lua: /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:777: /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:768: Vim:E1576: Tag file entry must not be a URL\n```\n\nThis error is introduced after commit `72bc6c` (#39461), where it disallows trying to open remote files. It seems like the tag for man pages (something like `man://ls(5)`) is considered to be a remote url in this context, and that's why it throws an error.\n\nRunning `:e man://ls(5)` shows the manpage without any errors.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n```\nand then run `:Man ls` within neovim.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nShow the manpage without errors.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.13.0-dev-364 g33ea63011c` neovim/neovim@33ea63011c\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.19.14_1\n- Terminal name/version: alacritty\n- $TERM environment variable: `alacritty`\n- Installation: ?",
